<title>USA: HFS Inc Q4 shr $0.33 vs $0.18.</title>
<headline>HFS Inc Q4 shr $0.33 vs $0.18.</headline>
<dateline>PARSIPPANY, N.J. 1997-01-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>1996			1995</p>
<p> Shr primary		$0.33		    $0.18</p>
<p> Net			 46,952		   20,366</p>
<p> Revs		     249,031		  113,252</p>
<p> Avg shrs primary     147,623		  120,810</p>
<p>	  12 MONTHS</p>
<p> Shr primary		$1.29		    $0.73</p>
<p> Net			169,584		   79,730</p>
<p> Revs		     799,040		  412,983</p>
<p> Avg shrs primary     135,310		  115,654</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>Note: During 1996 Q4, the company wrote off its investment in and receivable from Amre Inc, and recorded a gain related to the prepayment of a contractual arrangement with the company. Excluding the two transactions, HFS's earnings per share for Q4 1996 would have been $0.35/shr.  </p>
<p>Excluding the Q2 1996 $0.03 per share restructuring charge, related primarily to the creation of National Realty Trust, as well as the transactions recognized during 1996 Q4, full year 1996 earnings per share were $1.34/shr.</p>
<p>((--New York Newsdesk 212-859-1611))</p>
